channel.title: Overclocking?
channel.description:
Alright, well my computer is kinda old, but I made editions to it now the processor speed is lower than it use to be (runs at like 1.2Ghz, use to be 2 something). Editions: Ive upgraded from 512mb ram to 2gb Went from nvidia4 (i think) to ati x1650 pro
But my question is, how would I go about getting my processor back up to the speed it use to be? Do I need to overclock? How would I do that?
EDIT 9/21: Could it be my power supply why Its running under speed?

item.title: Overclocking?
item.dc:creator: @The_Un-Named The Un-Named
item.description:
@The_Un-Named wrote:

we need more info, list motherboard make/model, cpu make/model etc, you can use the program “speccy” to find this out

some things to consider, power savings mode often underclock processors to make HUGE savings on power usage etc, try running a prime95 test(don’t forget to close it) and see if the increased load increases the speed

also if you don’t mind can you provide some cpu-z screenshots, one idle and one with prime95 will be sufficient

edit: and most importantly, is it a laptop/notebook?

Read full topic
